Package: leechcraft-advancednotifications
Architecture: any
Depends: ${misc:Depends}, ${shlibs:Depends},
 libleechcraft-xmlsettingsdialog0.3.0 (= ${binary:Version}),
 libleechcraft-util0.5.0 (= ${binary:Version}),
 leechcraft (= ${binary:Version})
Recommends: leechcraft-provider-notifier-visual
Suggests: leechcraft-provider-mediaplayer
Description: Advanced Notifications framework for LeechCraft
 This plugin provides support for the notifications framework of the
 same name. It supports various notifiers like visual notifications,
 audio notifications, tray notifications and custom command execution.
 .
 It also allows one to define a list of rules for the events to be
 matched with, thus providing fine-grained notifications configuration
 for different events. For example, one could make it notify about IM
 messages from "Personal" group using all available methods, and notify
 about every message in a chosen conference using only visual
 notifications.
 .
 Advanced Notifications module contains a default set of rules pretty
 suitable for average use cases.
 .
 LeechCraft is a free modular "Internet client" application.
 .
 LeechCraft allows one to browse the web, read RSS/Atom feeds, download
 files via BitTorrent, HTTP, FTP and Direct Connect, automatically stream,
 download or play podcasts and other media files and much more.

Package: leechcraft-aggregator
Architecture: any
Depends: ${misc:Depends}, ${shlibs:Depends},
 libleechcraft-xmlsettingsdialog0.3.0 (= ${binary:Version}),
 libleechcraft-util0.5.0 (= ${binary:Version}),
 leechcraft (= ${binary:Version}),
 leechcraft-provider-http
Provides: leechcraft-provider-feedreader
Recommends: leechcraft-provider-webbrowser,
 leechcraft-provider-tasksview
Description: RSS/Atom feed reader for LeechCraft
 This package contains Aggregator, the RSS/Atom feed reader. It features:
  * RSS 0.92/0.93/1.0/2.0, Atom 0.3/1.0;
  * extensions like GeoRSS, MediaRSS, Comment API etc; 
  * OPML support;
  * broadcatching and fetching arbitrary data with regexps;
  * tape mode for news display;
  * individual options for each channel like update interval;
  * storage either in SQLite or PostgreSQL;
  * exporting feeds to FB2 for further reading on handheld devices.
 .
 A web browser plugin is recommended to show the news in a fancy way.
 .
 LeechCraft is a free modular "Internet client" application.
