Package: leechcraft-azoth
Architecture: any
Depends: ${misc:Depends}, ${shlibs:Depends},
 libleechcraft-xmlsettingsdialog0.3.0 (= ${binary:Version}),
 libleechcraft-util0.5.0 (= ${binary:Version}),
 leechcraft (= ${binary:Version}),
Recommends: telepathy-mission-control-5, telepathy-haze
Suggests: telepathy-butterfly, telepathy-rakia, telepathy-salut
Description: Modular IM client for LeechCraft
 This package contains the core of the Azoth plugin (the modular IM client for
 LeechCraft) and its own sub-plugins:
  * acetamide (IRC protocol support)
  * adiumstyles (Support for Adium styles)
  * astrality (Support for protocols provided by Telepathy)
    Telepathy is also hight modular system, you can use these modules:
    - butterfly (MSN connection manager)
    - haze (Connection manager based on libpurple)
      Libpurple (pidgin) currently supports such protocols:
      AIM/ICQ, Yahoo!, MSN, IRC, Jabber/XMPP/Google Talk, Napster, Zephyr,
      Gadu-Gadu, Bonjour, Groupwise, Sametime, SIMPLE, MySpaceIM, and MXit.
    - rakia (SIP connection manager)
    - salut (Provides Link-local Jabber functionality)
  * autopaste (Automatic paste of long messages to pastebins)
  * autoidler (Automatic changing of status according to idle time)
  * chathistory (History storage)
  * depester (Conference ignore plugin)
    This plugin allows one to ignore messages from selected multiuser
    chatroom participants, blocking both general messages in the room
    and private messages.
  * embedmedia (Embeds media files in the chat window)
    This plugin allows one to show various media objects (like videos from
    the YouTube service) directly in the chat window.
  * herbicide (Basic antispam plugin)
  * hili (Custom highlights)
    This plugin allows one to customize the highlight settings in multiuser
    chatrooms in Azoth. Highlights could be triggered by a plain string
    or by a regular expression.
  * isterique (Plugin for decapitalizing all-caps text)
  * juick (Plugin for the Juick.com service)
    This package contains Juick.com microblogging service plugin that
    enhances the experience of using the service.
  * lastseen (Plugin for keeping track of the date of contacts being online)
  * metacontacts (Support for metacontacts)
  * modnok (Plugin for rendering and displaying LaTeX formulas)
  * nativeemoticons (Support for emoticons packs)
    This plugin adds support for "standard" emoticons to Azoth.
  * otroid (Support Off-the-Record messaging)
  * p100q (Plugin for psto.net service)
    This package contains psto.net microblogging service plugin that
    enhances the experience of using the service.
  * rosenthal (Spellchecker plugin)
  * standardstyles (Standard styling support)
    Standard styling plugin that provides support for default (and pretty
    unimpressive) themes for chat windows.
  * vader (Support for the MRIM protocol)
  * xoox (XMPP/Jabber support)
    This package contains the XMPP protocol plugin for Azoth, based on the
    patched QXmpp library.
  * xtazy (Plugin for publishing current tune)
    This plugin allows one to publish current user tune. MPRIS-compatible
    players and standard files are supported as sources of information
    about current tune.
  * zheet (libmsn-based Windows Live protocol support)
 .
 LeechCraft is a free modular "Internet client" application.
 .
 LeechCraft allows one to browse the web, read RSS/Atom feeds, download
 files via BitTorrent, HTTP, FTP and Direct Connect, automatically stream,
 download or play podcasts and other media files and much more.

Package: leechcraft-bittorrent
Architecture: any
Depends: ${misc:Depends}, ${shlibs:Depends},
 libleechcraft-xmlsettingsdialog0.3.0 (= ${binary:Version}),
 libleechcraft-util0.5.0 (= ${binary:Version}),
 leechcraft (= ${binary:Version}),
 leechcraft-provider-tasksview
Provides: leechcraft-provider-bittorrent
Description: BitTorrent client for LeechCraft
 This package contains a sophisticated BitTorrent client. It's based on
 the Rasterbar Libtorrent library and features:
  * full support for protocol and extensions
  * DHT
  * magnet links
  * sequential download mode instead of default random one
  * ability to alter the directory structure and file names in torrents
  * selective downloads with per-file priorities
  * torrents queue with smart rotation depending on torrent's health
  * fast resume
  * speed limits and IP filter
 .
 LeechCraft is a free modular "Internet client" application.
